<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1490349-do-this-books-need-to-be-read-in-order">Do this books need to be read in order? I&#39;ve read the first and have the third. Wondering if it makes a difference.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1490349'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F35074316-her-last-goodbye">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1490349-do-this-books-need-to-be-read-in-order">3 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1490349-do-this-books-need-to-be-read-in-order">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/74716012-stephanie-mackey"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1512674497i/74716012._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/74716012-stephanie-mackey">Stephanie Mackey</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
Yes, they should be read in order. Not for the cases/crimes but for the personal developments in the lives of the main characters. 
</span>
</div>
