<div id="review_2126586540" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2126586540" />
    <a title="Terri ♥ (aka Mrs. Christian Grey)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6014919-terri-aka-mrs-christian-grey"><img alt="Terri ♥ (aka Mrs. Christian Grey)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1355500814p2/6014919.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2126586540?book_show_action=true">Oct 05, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Terri ♥ (aka Mrs. Christian Grey)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Terri ♥ (aka Mrs. Christian Grey)" href="/user/show/6014919-terri-aka-mrs-christian-grey">Terri ♥ (aka Mrs. Christian Grey)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/34873254-her-last-goodbye">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6014919-terri-aka-mrs-christian-grey?shelf=kindle-unlimited">kindle-unlimited</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6014919-terri-aka-mrs-christian-grey?shelf=audio">audio</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2126586540" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14616884250741572409">Though I didn’t pick the bad guy, I did pick the killer. Also, I knew based on other books there would be two seemingly interlocked cases. All in all, a solid read. No real complaints. I wonder if the siblings weren’t brought in for future spinoffs. Or maybe they already are as I didn’t connect Stella to this series at first. Nothing really more to say. It’s a lighter mystery with light romance, some sizzle and steamy but not overly descriptive. That doesn’t bother me. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

