    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3602448839" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3602448839" />
    <a title="Lauren" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4731410-lauren"><img alt="Lauren" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1387526203p2/4731410.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3602448839?book_show_action=true">Nov 23, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lauren" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lauren" href="/user/show/4731410-lauren">Lauren</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4731410-lauren?shelf=romantic-suspense">romantic-suspense</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4731410-lauren?shelf=kidnapping-hostage">kidnapping-hostage</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4731410-lauren?shelf=small-town">small-town</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4731410-lauren?shelf=serial-killers">serial-killers</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4731410-lauren?shelf=private-investigator-security">private-investigator-security</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4731410-lauren?shelf=widows-weeds">widows-weeds</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3602448839" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12534414013659626603"><b>Her Last Goodbye</b><br/>4 Stars<br/><br/>Defense Attorney Morgan Dare and her new partner, PI Lance Kruger, investigate the disappearance of a young wife and mother at the behest of her distraught husband, who is also the prime suspect. With few leads and little help from local law enforcement, Morgan and Lance delve deeper into the woman&apos;s life only to have Morgan and her family become a target for a deranged madman. <br/><br/>A gripping mystery with appealing characters, but there are certain aspects of Leigh&apos;s writing t</span>
  <span id="freeText12534414013659626603" style="display:none"><b>Her Last Goodbye</b><br />4 Stars<br /><br />Defense Attorney Morgan Dare and her new partner, PI Lance Kruger, investigate the disappearance of a young wife and mother at the behest of her distraught husband, who is also the prime suspect. With few leads and little help from local law enforcement, Morgan and Lance delve deeper into the woman's life only to have Morgan and her family become a target for a deranged madman. <br /><br />A gripping mystery with appealing characters, but there are certain aspects of Leigh's writing that I find problematic. These are personal preferences that others might not mind, so take them with a grain of salt. <br /><br />To begin with, there are some loose ends and inconsistencies within the narrative that make it difficult for the reader to follow the clues to the eventual revelation of the villain. While this does provide for some solid twists, it is the result of misleading the reader, which I personally dislike. <br /><br />These issues aside, the suspense plot is intense and exciting with an excellent climax and resolution. The slow-burn romance between Morgan and Lance is also engaging as they both approach their relationship in an adult and responsible way. Morgan is a strong and resilient heroine, and Lance, her partner in every sense of the word, clearly recognizes and accepts this. He provides her with both the professional and personal support that she needs. <br /><br />All in all, a great follow-up to the first book and I look forward to reading the next one. <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12534414013659626603" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


