<div id="review_2402237830" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2402237830" />
    <a title="Pat " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7407123-pat"><img alt="Pat " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1638757717p2/7407123.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2402237830?book_show_action=true">May 24, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pat " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pat " href="/user/show/7407123-pat">Pat </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2402237830" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3704236917752106842">3.5 stars. OK this was a bit better than the first book, it was slightly less cheesy. I don&apos;t like romance but I can handle romantic suspense or thrillers as long as the romance takes a back seat. This book may have been borderline but it did hold my interest until the end.<br/><br/>A young mother of two disappears. The husband did it, right? The husband doesn&apos;t trust the police to investigate other suspects thoroughly so he seeks help from Morgan Dane. I&apos;m not really sure shy as she is a lawyer not a PI.</span>
  <span id="freeText3704236917752106842" style="display:none">3.5 stars. OK this was a bit better than the first book, it was slightly less cheesy. I don't like romance but I can handle romantic suspense or thrillers as long as the romance takes a back seat. This book may have been borderline but it did hold my interest until the end.<br /><br />A young mother of two disappears. The husband did it, right? The husband doesn't trust the police to investigate other suspects thoroughly so he seeks help from Morgan Dane. I'm not really sure shy as she is a lawyer not a PI. Fortunately her love interest IS a PI so they join forces again to solve this case. For a lawyer, Morgan doesn't do much lawyering, never mind, whatever moves the plot along. It was an OK story and I will persevere and try one more in this series.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3704236917752106842" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
